chemaxon.marvin.modules
Interface MoleculeIterators.BondIteratorInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
MacroMolecule.Polymer.BondIterator, MoleculeIterators.MoleculeBondIterator
Enclosing interface:
MoleculeIterators
public static interface MoleculeIterators.BondIteratorInterface

Classes that implement the BondIteratorInterface interface enumerate bonds of a molecule. Such molecule is not exclusively the instance of the Molecule, as for instance components of a MacroMolecule object can also be considered as molecules.
A bond iterator that implements this interface does not neccesarily lists all bonds of the molecule but a subset specified by further methods provided by the particular bond iterator though not required by this interface (e.g. main chain bonds of protein).

next

public void next()
Skips to next bond. This has no effect if hasNext() returned false. As multiple propreties correspond to the current bond no value is returned by this method.

getX

public float getX(int whichAtom)
Gets the first coordinate of the atom at the specified end of the current bond. An undefined neighbor can also be queried (when the given parameter value is NEIGHBOR). This neighbouring atom is connected to either end of the bond. This is needed for 3D drawing.

Parameters:
whichAtom - ATOM1 or ATOM2 or NEIGHBOR
Returns:
x coordinate of the atom at the specified end of the bond
